nd of the conjuring of Cravan in Picabia’s elegiac film Entr’acte – The fictions of Arthur Cravan concludes with the absent poet-boxer’s eventual casting off into a Surrealist legacy, and his becoming what metaphor is: a means to represent the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDadaism. 0aSurrealism. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Historical.2bisacsh  aArthur Cravan.  aDada.  aDeleuze.  aNietzsche.  aSurrealism.  ametaphor.  amultiplicity.  arepresentation.  asimulation.  asubjectivity.1 aJones, Dafydd W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2019 eBook-Packagez978311128249740uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152613324340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526133243423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526133243/original  a978-3-11-128249-7  Manchester University Press 2019 eBook-Packageb2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles